` only when `skim` is too thin, ambiguous, or you need exact evidence:\n    34\t\n    35\t```sh\n    36\tbut agentlog show <session-key> --limit 20\n    37\tbut agentlog show <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n    38\t```\n    39\t\n    40\tFor normal current-branch recovery, run `skim` without target arguments first.\n    41\tIt discovers the applied GitButler branch itself. Do not run plain Git commands\n    42\tlike `git\n[TRUNCATED]\n\t```\n   137\t\n   138\tWithout `--turn`, `show` answers what happened in a session at turn granularity.\n   139\t\n   140\tUseful fields:\n   141\t\n   142\t- `coverage`: returned turns versus total turns.\n   143\t- `turn_key`: handle for `show --turn`.\n   144\t- `turn_index`: order within the session.\n   145\t- `capture_kind`: backfill or incremental.\n   146\t- `record_count`: turn size before hydrating records.\n   147\t- `source_record_index_range`: provider/source indexes covered by the turn.\n   148\t- `observed_targets`: targets observed in the turn.\n   149\t- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: compact orientation.\n   150\t- `tool_counts`: tool call/result counts and tool names.\n   151\t\n   152\tIncrease `--limit` only when the current window misses the related turn or setup.\n   153\t\n   154\tWith `--turn`, `show` answers what exactly happened inside one turn.\n   155\t\n   156\tUseful record fields:\n   157\t\n   158\t- `coverage`: returned records versus total records in the turn.\n   159\t- `turn_record_index`: order within the turn.\n   160\t- `source_record_index`: original provider/source index when available.\n   161\t- `timestamp`, `kind`, `role`, `text`: message/tool orientation.\n   162\t- `tool_name` and `tool_input`: tool details when present.\n   163\t- `source_record`: redacted stored provider envelope for low-level debugging.\n   164\t\n   165\tTurn records are intentionally bounded. Increase `--limit` only for a specific\n   166\tturn after session-level `show` output proves that more detail is needed.\n   167\t\n   168\t## Skim Summary\n   169\t\n   170\tWhen summarizing a skim, do not say you recovered \"full context.\" Say you\n   171\tskimmed the full turn history in abbreviated form.\n   172\t\n   173\tInclude:\n   174\t\n   175\t- target used for discovery\n   176\t- previews explaining intent and outcome\n   177\t- minimal record snippets for the next action\n   178\t\n   179\tDo not lead with raw session or turn identifiers. Mention them only when the\n   180\tuser asks for evidence handles or when passing them to another command/tool.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T05:40:10.671Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}